The article discusses the Open Government Partnership (OGP), an international partnership between governments and civil society to promote transparency, fight corruption, and leverage technology to open up governments worldwide. The OGP has grown from 8 to 65 nations and has generated over 2,000 new national commitments to improve government for more than 2 billion people. The article highlights various initiatives announced by President Obama to promote open government, including promoting open education, delivering government services more effectively through information technology, increasing transparency in spending, and using big data to support openness and accountability. These initiatives aim to increase citizen engagement, improve government services, and ensure privacy protection.